zaffino as key lieutenant  nd update by leslie scism published july   features dow jones newswires facebook twitter print american international group inc chief executive brian duperreault has hired former marsh  mclennan cos colleague peter zaffino to be one of his top lieutenants his first highprofile recruit since joining the insurance giant in may continue reading below mr zaffino will start as executive vice president and global chief operating officer on aug  he comes to aig after six years as ceo of marsh  mclennans marsh brokerage unit he was also chairman of marsh  mclennans risk and insuranceservices operation mr duperreault was ceo of marsh  mclennan from  to  mr zaffinos selection was first reported by trade publication insurance insider mr zaffino is expected to become a key part of a team tasked with improving aigs profit margins after years in which the company has trailed many peers continue reading below advertisement some of its woes stem from its near collapse in the  global financial crisis a us government bailout required it to sell off some prized businesses to fully repay nearly  billion provided by taxpayers mr duperreault was named to the top job after a profitimprovement plan championed by the previous aig chief executive peter hancock fell behind schedule some activist investors  including carl icahn who has a representative on aigs board  last year called for the insurance conglomerate to improve its results by splitting itself apart but those investors have given aig some leeway to improve returns using other methods mr hancocks strategy was to eliminate or shrink lines of business that didnt meet profitmargin targets cut costs and return  billion to shareholders through buybacks and dividends thus far mr duperreault has said he is open to slowing down the firms share buybacks and instead using the capital for acquisitions he also has said he wont split up aig and instead pledged to grow it he has said he doesnt have specific acquisitions in mind but was open for business and believes there are lots of growth opportunities internationally in particular write to leslie scism at lesliescismwsjcom end dow jones newswires july    et  gmt aig ceo taps peter zaffino as key lieutenant  fox business fox business aig ceo taps peter zaffino as key lieutenant advertisement on our radar refresh close on our radar aig ceo taps peter zaffino as key lieutenant by leslie scism published july   features dow jones newswires facebook twitter print new american international group inc chief executive brian duperreault has hired former marsh  mclennan cos colleague peter zaffino to be one of his top lieutenants according to people familiar with the matter continue reading below it is mr duperreaults first highprofile recruit since joining the insurance giant in may mr zaffino most recently was ceo of marsh  mclennans marsh brokerage unit a job he held starting in  he was also chairman of marsh  mclennans risk and insuranceservices operation mr duperreault was ceo of marsh  mclennan from  to  mr zaffinos selection was first reported by trade publication insurance insider mr zaffino is expected to become a key part of a team tasked with improving aigs profit margins after years in which the company has trailed many peers continue reading below advertisement some of its woes stem from its near collapse in the  global financial crisis a us government bailout required it to sell off some prized businesses to fully repay nearly  billion provided by taxpayers mr duperreault was named to the top job after a profitimprovement plan championed by the previous aig chief executive peter hancock fell behind schedule some activist investors  including carl icahn who has a representative on aigs board  last year called for the insurance conglomerate to improve its results by splitting itself apart but those investors have given aig some leeway to improve returns using other methods mr hancocks strategy was to eliminate or shrink lines of business that didnt meet profitmargin targets cut costs and return  billion to shareholders through buybacks and dividends thus far mr duperreault has said he is open to slowing down the firms share buybacks and instead using the capital for acquisitions he also has said he wont split up aig and instead pledged to grow it he has said he doesnt have specific acquisitions in mind but was open for business and believes there are lots of growth opportunities internationally in particular write to leslie scism at lesliescismwsjcom end dow jones newswires july    et  gmt peter zaffino  wikipedia peter zaffino from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search peter zaffino born january  greenwich connecticut nationality american education boston college ba new york university mba occupation global coo of aig predecessor jeffrey hurd parents salvatore d zaffino and marion zaffino peter zaffino born january  is an insurance industry leader and executive named evp and global chief operating officer of aig in july  prior to his appointment at aig zaffino served as chief executive officer of marsh and chairman of marsh  mclennan companies risk  insurance services segment which includes marsh a risk advisor and insurance broker and guy carpenter and company a reinsurance intermediary contents  early life and education  career  boards  references early life and educationedit zaffino holds a ba in economics from boston college and an mba in finance from new york universitys leonard n stern school of business he holds the cpcu and associate in reinsurance designations careeredit before his tenure at aig zaffinos career included several leadership roles at marsh  mclennan companies a professional services firm that ranked  on the  fortune  list prior to becoming ceo of marsh he was president and ceo of guy carpenter zaffino was appointed to lead marsh in early  and his responsibilities were expanded to include risk  insurance services in early  under zaffinos leader